{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EjwKSg3At3z7qoA7cohG89","type":"tool_result","content":"558\t\n559\t**Strengths:** Clean module boundaries, complete file migration plan, dependency chain breaks documented, official SDK replaces bash spawning, beads-level state simplicity, structural evaluator isolation.\n560\t\n561\t**Key risk:** Beads cleanup touches 12 files — must be done atomically to avoid broken imports. Recommended: delete beads.ts + beads-sync.ts first, then fix all compiler errors in one pass.\n562\t\n563\t### AD6: Issue Tracking (Beads Replacement)\n564\t\n565\t**Problem:** Beads is removed but the underlying need remains — retro findings, bugs, and tech debt need a path from \"discovered\" to \"scheduled\" to \"implemented.\" BMAD handles planned stories well but not unplanned issues.\n566\t\n567\t**Decision:** Simple `issues.yaml` file parallel to `sprint-status.yaml`.\n568\t\n569\t```yaml\n570\t# .codeharness/issues.yaml (or _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/issues.yaml)\n571\tissues:\n572\t  - id: issue-001\n573\t    title: Docker timeout handling too aggressive\n574\t    source: retro-epic-15       # where it came from\n575\t    priority: high\n576\t    status: ready-for-dev       # same statuses as stories\n577\t  - id: issue-002\n578\t    title: Evaluator too lenient on API error codes\n579\t    source: manual\n580\t    priority: medium\n581\t    status: backlog\n582\t```\n583\t\n584\t**How it works:**\n585\t- `codeharness issue create \"title\" --priority high --source retro-epic-15` → adds to issues.yaml\n586\t- Retro workflow tags findings as `actionable: true` → auto-added to issues.yaml\n587\t- Workflow engine reads both `sprint-status.yaml` (stories) AND `issues.yaml` (issues)\n588\t- Issues interleaved into execution based on priority\n589\t- Same statuses, same execution path, same verification — the engine doesn't distinguish stories from issues\n590\t\n591\t**Rationale:** File-based, no external dependencies, beads-level simplicity. Everything goes through the workflow engine. No separate issue tracker to maintain. Retro findings get a mechanical path to implementation instead of rotting in markdown.\n592\t\n593\t**Implementation Priority:**\n594\t1. Beads cleanup (unblock everything — 12 files, surgical removal)\n595\t2. Legacy deletion (ralph/, hooks/, old verify/proof modules)\n596\t3. New modules in dependency order (state → parser → resolver → dispatch → engine → evaluator → circuit-breaker)\n597\t4. Command rework (run.ts, verify.ts, init.ts, status.ts)\n598\t5. Skills and plugin.json update\n599\t6. Integration tests\n600\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XpaP1HRJV63HnT5Mxey4dk","session_id":"3f15b50c-2c9b-40fa-9e63-9fad2199af43","uuid":"f6ae72fb-d7c6-448a-ac9d-12dd8eaedef1","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:17:53.495Z"}
