{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J56qjA1toXWR6s3p7pSTnK","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03\n2\t\n3\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T00:25 to ~2026-04-03T02:00 (approx. 95 minutes)\n4\t**Sprint progress:** 14/28 stories done (50%), Epics 1-4 complete\n5\t\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\t## 1. Session Summary\n9\t\n10\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n11\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n12\t| 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection | verify (tail end) | **Done** | Was already at verify from prior session. 9/9 ACs passed. |\n13\t| 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement | create-story, dev, code-review, verify | **Done** | Full lifecycle in one session. 9/9 ACs, 100% coverage on module. |\n14\t| Epic 4 milestone | — | **Done** | All 4 stories shipped. Commit `4a35568`. |\n15\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | create-story, dev | **Review** | Story created and implemented. 31 tests, 89.91% coverage. Ran out of time before code-review/verify. |\n16\t\n17\t**Net output:** 2 stories completed + verified, 1 story implemented but not reviewed, 1 epic closed.\n18\t\n19\t---\n20\t\n21\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n22\t\n23\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n24\t\n25\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n26\t|----------|-------|-------|\n27\t| HIGH | 4-3 | `generateTraceId` accepted NaN/Infinity/negative/float iteration values |\n28\t| HIGH | 4-4 | Path traversal via unsanitized `runId` in file path |\n29\t| HIGH | 4-4 | Silent file overwrite on basename collision — data loss risk |\n30\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | No segment length cap — unbounded trace IDs possible |\n31\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | `formatTracePrompt('')` produced empty trace marker silently |\n32\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | `workflow-state.ts` coverage at 79.06%, below 80% floor |\n33\t| MEDIUM | 4-4 | Stale workspace contamination from crashed runs |\n34\t| MEDIUM | 4-4 | Missing edge case tests for sanitization/dedup |\n35\t\n36\tAll HIGH and MEDIUM bugs were fixed in the same session. Code review is earning its keep — 3 HIGH security/correctness bugs caught before merge.\n37\t\n38\t### Known LOW Issues (deferred)\n39\t\n40\t- 4-3: Duplicate trace ID guard missing; empty runId+taskName produces ugly ID; sanitizeSegment strips non-ASCII\n41\t- 4-4: `deduplicateFilename` counter loop unbounded; hardcoded `/tmp/` base path\n42\t\n43\t### Infrastructure Issues\n44\t\n45\t- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure:** The verify command checks global harness state flags (`tests_passed`, `coverage_met`) which are not set by manual test runs. Workaround: verify manually. This is a harness tooling gap.\n46\t- **`AGENTS.md` stale:** Verify command flags missing entries for new modules (`agent-dispatch.ts`, `agent-resolver.ts`, `session-manager.ts`, `trace-id.ts`, `source-isolation.ts`). Documentation debt accumulating — 5 modules behind now.\n47\t- **Pre-existing TS errors:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 pre-existing type errors unrelated to current work.\n48\t\n49\t---\n50\t\n51\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n52\t\n53\t### Parent-Level Costs (from cost-report.md, prior session data)\n54\t\n55\tThe cost report covers the prior session (stories through Epic 2). Key structural observations:\n56\t\n57\t- **Total API cost:** $37.08 across 288 calls for 7 stories\n58\t- **Avg cost/story:** $4.45\n59\t- **Dominant cost:** Cache reads at 61% ($22.62) — expected for long-context sessions\n60\t- **Verify phase:** 43.8% of total cost ($16.24) — nearly half of all spending is on verification"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XpaP1HRJV63HnT5Mxey4dk","session_id":"3f15b50c-2c9b-40fa-9e63-9fad2199af43","uuid":"6b799360-bf1c-421f-a08b-5eaf7481ca9b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:18:09.106Z"}
