{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XpaP1HRJV63HnT5Mxey4dk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created. Per the user's instructions, I am NOT modifying sprint-status.yaml, NOT running git add, and NOT running git commit.\n\n---\n\n**Story Details:**\n- Story ID: 8.2\n- Story Key: 8-2-retro-finding-auto-import\n- File: `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-2-retro-finding-auto-import.md`\n- Status: ready-for-dev\n\n**Next Steps:**\n1. Review the story file\n2. Run `dev-story` for implementation\n3. Run `code-review` when complete\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` does not exist at the expected path; it's at `_bmad/config.yaml` instead. The workflow.yaml references `{project-root}/_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` which is wrong.\n- The workflow file was `.yaml` not `.md` as referenced in the skill instructions — the skill said to load `workflow.md` but only `workflow.yaml` exists.\n- FR42 in `prd.md` (\"System can apply harness patches to BMAD story templates\") is completely different from FR42 in `epics-v2.md` (\"Retro findings tagged as actionable are automatically added to issues.yaml\"). Used epics-v2.md as the source of truth since it's the v2 planning artifact.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- The retro file format varies between older (table) and newer (subsection) formats. Both parsers already exist in `retro-parser.ts`. The story specifies a fallback strategy: try subsections first, then table format.\n- The existing `retro-import.ts` has a `retro-to-sprint.ts` module that creates TD-* stories in sprint-state.json — a completely different system from the issues.yaml tracker. The story explicitly warns against using that module.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC5 (table-format fallback) relies on `derivePriority()` which maps to numbers (1/2) not strings. The dev agent needs to map 1->\"high\", 2->\"medium\" correctly.\n- The older retro files use `| # | Action | Priority | Notes |` headers (different column names than the parser expects: `| # | Action | Status | Notes |`). The `parseRetroActionItems` parser looks for `Status` not `Priority` in the header regex. Some retro files may not parse correctly with the table parser. This is a pre-existing issue in the parser, not something for this story to fix.\n\n**Observations:**\n- The codebase has two parallel retro-to-issue pipelines: `retro-to-sprint.ts` (creates TD-* sprint stories) and the retro-import command (creates GitHub issues). This story adds a third path (issues.yaml). The three systems are not unified, which could cause confusion. However, the v2 architecture (AD6) clearly intends issues.yaml as the canonical path.\n- All the building blocks already exist — this story is essentially wiring together `retro-parser.ts` + `issue-tracker.ts` inside `retro-import.ts`. No new modules needed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 20\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 13, Glob: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 16 unique, 16 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — one Glob for `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` returned empty before finding it at `_bmad/config.yaml`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afeff8788f289220b (use SendMessage with to: 'afeff8788f289220b' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74009\ntool_uses: 40\nduration_ms: 291795</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f15b50c-2c9b-40fa-9e63-9fad2199af43","uuid":"3e8871c3-ca5c-4035-8e76-84c4434b304f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:21:00.443Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-create-story for story 8-2-retro-finding-auto-import. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification 