{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BQuBkDb4RZHg8DqqMcBDUf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 8.2: Retro Finding Auto-Import\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want retro findings tagged as actionable (Fix Now / Fix Soon) to be automatically added to `.codeharness/issues.yaml`,\n11\tso that action items from retrospectives don't rot in markdown and instead enter the issue tracker for scheduled execution.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a retrospective file with a `## 6. Action Items` section containing `### Fix Now` and `### Fix Soon` subsections with bullet items\n16\t   **When** `codeharness retro-import --epic <n>` runs\n17\t   **Then** each Fix Now and Fix Soon item is added to `.codeharness/issues.yaml` via the issue tracker module with `source: \"retro-epic-<n>\"`, `status: backlog`\n18\t   **And** Fix Now items get `priority: high`\n19\t   **And** Fix Soon items get `priority: medium`\n20\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n21\t\n22\t2. **Given** a retrospective file with a `### Backlog` subsection under Action Items\n23\t   **When** `codeharness retro-import --epic <n>` runs\n24\t   **Then** Backlog items are NOT added to `.codeharness/issues.yaml`\n25\t   **And** they are still logged to console as skipped (non-actionable)\n26\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n27\t\n28\t3. **Given** `.codeharness/issues.yaml` already contains an issue with title matching a retro action item (word overlap >= 0.8)\n29\t   **When** `codeharness retro-import --epic <n>` runs with a duplicate item\n30\t   **Then** the duplicate item is skipped with an informational message\n31\t   **And** the existing issue is not modified\n32\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n33\t\n34\t4. **Given** no `.codeharness/issues.yaml` exists\n35\t   **When** `codeharness retro-import --epic <n>` runs with actionable items\n36\t   **Then** `.codeharness/issues.yaml` is created with the imported issues\n37\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t5. **Given** a retrospective file with no `## 6. Action Items` section (table-only format with `| # | Action | Status | Notes |`)\n40\t   **When** `codeharness retro-import --epic <n>` runs\n41\t   **Then** items from the table are still parsed and imported using the existing `parseRetroActionItems` parser\n42\t   **And** priority is derived from status/notes fields via `derivePriority` (regressed/urgent/critical -> high, default -> medium)\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t6. **Given** `codeharness retro-import --epic <n> --json` runs\n46\t   **When** the import completes\n47\t   **Then** JSON output includes `imported` count, `skipped` count, `duplicates` count, and an `issues` array with each imported issue's `id`, `title`, `source`, `priority`\n48\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t7. **Given** the retro file does not exist\n51\t   **When** `codeharness retro-import --epic <n>` runs\n52\t   **Then** it prints an error message and exits with code 1\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t8. **Given** the retro file has no action items (empty table and no subsections)\n56\t   **When** `codeharness retro-import --epic <n>` runs\n57\t   **Then** it prints \"No action items found in retro file\" and exits with code 0\n58\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n59\t\n60\t9. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n61\t   **When** the build completes\n62\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero errors\n63\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n64\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n65\t\n66\t10. **Given** unit tests for the retro-import changes\n67\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n68\t    **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for modified code covering: section-based import, table-based import, duplicate detection, priority mapping, JSON output, error handling\n69\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n70\t\n71\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n72\t\n73\t- [x] Task 1: Update `src/commands/retro-import.ts` to import actionable findings into issues.yaml (AC: #1, #2, #4, #5, #6, #7, #8)\n74\t  - [x] Import `createIssue`, `readIssues` from `../lib/issue-tracker.js`\n75\t  - [x] Import `parseRetroSections`, `isDuplicate` from `../lib/retro-parser.js`\n76\t  - [x] After parsing action items, attempt section-based parsing via `parseRetroSections(content)`\n77\t  - [x] If section-based items found (Fix Now / Fix Soon): import those into issues.yaml\n78\t  - [x] If only table-based items found: import those using `derivePriority` for priority mapping\n79\t  - [x] Map Fix Now -> `priority: high`, Fix Soon -> `priority: medium`\n80\t  - [x] Map table-based priorities: `derivePriority` returns 1 -> `high`, 2 -> `medium`\n81\t  - [x] Set `source: \"retro-epic-<n>\"` on all imported issues\n82\t  - [x] Skip Backlog items (log as non-actionable)\n83\t  - [x] Remove or replace the `TODO: v2 issue tracker (Epic 8)` comment at line 89\n84\t  - [x] Replace the dead-code `imported = 0` / `skipped = 0` block with actual import logic\n85\t  - [x] Update JSON output to include `imported`, `skipped`, `duplicates` counts and `issues` array\n86\t\n87\t- [x] Task 2: Add duplicate detection before import (AC: #3)\n88\t  - [x] Before creating each issue, read existing issue titles from `readIssues()`\n89\t  - [x] Use `isDuplicate(itemTitle, existingTitles)` from `retro-parser.ts` with 0.8 threshold\n90\t  - [x] If duplicate detected, skip and increment `duplicates` counter, log match info\n91\t\n92\t- [x] Task 3: Update `src/commands/__tests__/retro-import.test.ts` (AC: #9, #10)\n93\t  - [x] Add mock for `../lib/issue-tracker.js` (`createIssue`, `readIssues`)\n94\t  - [x] Test: section-based retro with Fix Now items creates issues with priority=high\n95\t  - [x] Test: section-based retro with Fix Soon items creates issues with priority=medium\n96\t  - [x] Test: Backlog items are skipped (not imported)\n97\t  - [x] Test: table-based retro (no subsections) falls back to table parser + derivePriority\n98\t  - [x] Test: duplicate detection skips matching items\n99\t  - [x] Test: no issues.yaml creates new file via createIssue\n100\t  - [x] Test: JSON output includes imported/skipped/duplicates counts\n101\t  - [x] Test: missing retro file → error with exit code 1\n102\t  - [x] Test: empty retro file → info message, exit code 0\n103\t\n104\t- [x] Task 4: Verify build and all tests pass (AC: #9)\n105\t  - [x] Run `npm run build` — zero errors\n106\t  - [x] Run `npm run test:unit` — no regressions\n107\t\n108\t## Dev Notes\n109\t\n110\t### Architecture Context\n111\t\n112\tThis story wires together three existing modules:\n113\t\n114\t1. **`retro-parser.ts`** — already has both parsers:\n115\t   - `parseRetroActionItems(content)` — table format (`| # | Action | Status | Notes |`)\n116\t   - `parseRetroSections(content)` — subsection format (`## 6. Action Items` → `### Fix Now` / `### Fix Soon` / `### Backlog`)\n117\t   - `isDuplicate(newItem, existingTitles, threshold=0.8)` — word-overlap deduplication\n118\t   - `derivePriority(item)` — maps status/notes to priority number (1 or 2)\n119\t\n120\t2. **`issue-tracker.ts`** (from story 8.1) — CRUD for `.codeharness/issues.yaml`:\n121\t   - `createIssue(title, { priority, source }, dir)` — creates and persists\n122\t   - `readIssues(dir)` — returns `{ issues: Issue[] }`\n123\t   - Valid priorities: `low`, `medium`, `high`, `critical`\n124\t\n125\t3. **`retro-import.ts`** (existing command) — currently:\n126\t   - Parses retro table format only\n127\t   - Creates GitHub issues via `gh` CLI\n128\t   - Has a `TODO: v2 issue tracker (Epic 8)` placeholder (line 89)\n129\t   - Does NOT write to issues.yaml — this story adds that\n130\t\n131\t### Retro File Formats\n132\t\n133\tTwo formats exist across retro files:\n134\t\n135\t**Table format** (older retros like epic-7):\n136\t```markdown\n137\t## Action Items\n138\t\n139\t| # | Action | Priority | Notes |\n140\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n141\t| A1 | Fix X | Medium | Carried from epic 6 |\n142\t```\n143\t\n144\t**Subsection format** (newer retros):\n145\t```markdown\n146\t## 6. Action Items\n147\t\n148\t### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n149\t- Fix bare catch blocks in registry.ts\n150\t\n151\t### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n152\t1. Add element type checking to isValidState()\n153\t\n154\t### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n155\t- Remove StackDetection type duplication\n156\t```\n157\t\n158\tThe command must handle BOTH formats. Strategy:\n159\t1. Try `parseRetroSections(content)` first\n160\t2. If it returns items, use those (Fix Now -> high, Fix Soon -> medium, skip Backlog)\n161\t3. If no section items found, fall back to `parseRetroActionItems(content)` + `derivePriority()`\n162\t\n163\t### Priority Mapping\n164\t\n165\t| Retro Source | Issue Priority |\n166\t|-------------|---------------|\n167\t| Fix Now subsection | `high` |\n168\t| Fix Soon subsection | `medium` |\n169\t| Backlog subsection | NOT imported |\n170\t| Table: derivePriority returns 1 | `high` |\n171\t| Table: derivePriority returns 2 | `medium` |\n172\t\n173\t### Duplicate Detection\n174\t\n175\tUse `isDuplicate()` from `retro-parser.ts` which computes word overlap. Before calling `createIssue()`, read all existing issue titles and check each new item. Threshold is 0.8 (80% word overlap = duplicate).\n176\t\n177\t### Source Tag Format\n178\t\n179\tAll imported issues get `source: \"retro-epic-<n>\"` where `<n>` is the epic number from `--epic`. This matches the convention in the architecture doc (AD6): `source: retro-epic-15`.\n180\t\n181\t### GitHub Issue Phase\n182\t\n183\tThe existing GitHub issue creation phase stays intact. The local issues.yaml import happens BEFORE the GitHub phase. Both paths run independently — local import failures should not block GitHub creation and vice versa.\n184\t\n185\t### CLI Pattern\n186\t\n187\tFollow the existing command pattern in `retro-import.ts`:\n188\t- Use `ok()`, `fail()`, `info()`, `warn()` from `src/lib/output.ts`\n189\t- Support `--json` global flag via `cmd.optsWithGlobals()`\n190\t- Set `process.exitCode = 1` on errors (do NOT call `process.exit()`)\n191\t\n192\t### File Changes\n193\t\n194\t- **Modified:** `src/commands/retro-import.ts` — add issues.yaml import logic (~40-60 lines added)\n195\t- **Modified:** `src/commands/__tests__/retro-import.test.ts` — add tests for import path (~100-150 lines added)\n196\t- **No new files** — all required modules already exist\n197\t- **No new npm dependencies** — uses existing `yaml`, `retro-parser`, `issue-tracker`\n198\t\n199\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n200\t\n201\t- **Do NOT modify `retro-parser.ts`** — both parsers already work correctly\n202\t- **Do NOT modify `issue-tracker.ts`** — the createIssue API already handles everything needed\n203\t- **Do NOT remove the GitHub issue phase** — it runs independently of local import\n204\t- **Do NOT use `retro-to-sprint.ts`** — that module creates TD-* stories in sprint-state.json, which is a different system. This story uses the issues.yaml tracker from story 8.1\n205\t- **Do NOT use `process.exit()`** — set `process.exitCode` instead\n206\t- **Do NOT use `any`** in the API surface — explicit TypeScript types per NFR18\n207\t\n208\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n209\t\n210\tFrom story 8.1 (issue tracker module):\n211\t- `createIssue(title, { priority, source })` validates priority against `VALID_PRIORITIES` set\n212\t- Valid priorities are: `low`, `medium`, `high`, `critical` — map retro priorities accordingly\n213\t- `createIssue` auto-generates sequential IDs (`issue-NNN`)\n214\t- `readIssues()` returns `{ issues: [] }` if file doesn't exist\n215\t- Issues are stored at `.codeharness/issues.yaml` relative to cwd\n216\t\n217\tFrom existing `retro-import.ts`:\n218\t- Line 89: `// TODO: v2 issue tracker (Epic 8)` — this is the placeholder for this story\n219\t- Lines 90-92: `imported = 0`, `skipped = 0`, `issues: ImportedIssue[] = []` — dead code to replace\n220\t- The command already handles retro file discovery, parsing, and error handling\n221\t- GitHub phase (lines 121-132) should remain untouched\n222\t\n223\t### Git Intelligence\n224\t\n225\tRecent commits follow: `feat: story {key} — {description}`. The latest commit `f3f552e` implemented story 8.1. This story modifies one existing command file and its tests — no new files needed.\n226\t\n227\t### References\n228\t\n229\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 8.2: Retro Finding Auto-Import]\n230\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD6: Issue Tracking (Beads Replacement)]\n231\t- [Source: src/commands/retro-import.ts — TODO at line 89, GitHub phase at lines 121-132]\n232\t- [Source: src/lib/retro-parser.ts — parseRetroSections(), parseRetroActionItems(), isDuplicate(), derivePriority()]\n233\t- [Source: src/lib/issue-tracker.ts — createIssue(), readIssues(), VALID_PRIORITIES]\n234\t- [Source: src/lib/output.ts — ok(), fail(), info(), warn(), jsonOutput()]\n235\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-7-retrospective.md — table-format example]\n236\t\n237\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n238\t## Verification Requirements\n239\t\n240\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/8-2-retro-finding-auto-import-proof.md)\n241\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n242\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n243\t\n244\t## Documentation Requirements\n245\t\n246\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n247\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/8-2-retro-finding-auto-import.md\n248\t\n249\t## Testing Requirements\n250\t\n251\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n252\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n253\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n254\t\n255\t## Dev Agent Record\n256\t\n257\t### Agent Model Used\n258\t\n259\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n260\t\n261\t### Debug Log References\n262\t\n263\tNone.\n264\t\n265\t### Completion Notes List\n266\t\n267\t- Added `importToIssuesYaml()` function to `retro-import.ts` that handles both section-based and table-based retro formats\n268\t- Section-based: Fix Now -> high, Fix Soon -> medium, Backlog -> skipped\n269\t- Table-based fallback: uses `derivePriority()` (1 -> high, 2 -> medium)\n270\t- Duplicate detection via `isDuplicate()` with 0.8 word overlap threshold\n271\t- All issues get `source: \"retro-epic-<n>\"` and `status: backlog`\n272\t- GitHub phase remains untouched and independent\n273\t- 33 tests passing (up from 22), all 4172 unit tests pass, build clean\n274\t\n275\t### File List\n276\t\n277\t- `src/commands/retro-import.ts` — added local issues.yaml import logic (~90 lines added)\n278\t- `src/commands/__tests__/retro-import.test.ts` — added 11 new test cases covering section-based import, table-based fallback, duplicate detection, JSON output, error handling\n279\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01U1QxzZy7C659GJM4oxEmEf","session_id":"3f15b50c-2c9b-40fa-9e63-9fad2199af43","uuid":"cba58b03-de72-4c92-bb55-b7c5942d98cb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:27:20.468Z"}
