{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015TfapLQf9X3KEJmSgBiWvG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Tbq8uvPR9dftszWB5nuigP","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Verify story 8-2 runtime-provable","prompt":"Verify story 8-2-retro-finding-auto-import using local runtime checks (runtime-provable tier).\n\nStory file: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-2-retro-finding-auto-import.md\n\nExecute these steps and report results:\n1. Run the project build command (npm run build). Report: PASS or FAIL + first 10 error lines.\n2. Run tests (npm test). Report: PASS (N passed) or FAIL (N failed: list names).\n3. The project is a Node.js CLI tool. The run command is `node dist/index.js` (or check package.json \"bin\" field).\n4. Start the application or use it as a CLI tool. For this story, the relevant CLI commands are:\n   - `codeharness retro-import` — this is the command being tested\n   - `codeharness issue list` — to verify issues were created\n5. For each AC in the story file, verify it by interacting with the built CLI:\n   - AC1: Run retro-import on a retro file with section-based format containing \"Fix Now\" items. Verify issues are created in .codeharness/issues.yaml with priority: high.\n   - AC2: Run retro-import on a retro file with \"Fix Soon\" items. Verify priority: medium.\n   - AC3: Verify \"Backlog\" items are skipped (not imported).\n   - AC4: Run retro-import twice on the same retro file. Verify duplicates are detected and skipped.\n   - AC5: Run retro-import on a retro file with table-based format (older format). Verify it falls back and imports correctly.\n   - AC6: Verify imported issues have `source: \"retro-epic-<n>\"` field.\n   - AC7: Run retro-import with --json flag. Verify JSON output includes imported, skipped, duplicates counts.\n   - AC8: Verify .codeharness/issues.yaml file is created/updated with valid YAML.\n   - AC9: Check unit tests exist and pass for all import paths.\n   - AC10: Verify the retro-import command integrates with the existing issue-tracker module.\n   Report each AC as PASS or FAIL with one-line evidence.\n\nIMPORTANT: To set up test data, create temporary retro files in /tmp for testing. Example section-based format:\n```markdown\n## Action Items\n\n### Fix Now\n- Fix the broken parser module\n- Update error handling in CLI\n\n### Fix Soon  \n- Refactor duplicate detection logic\n\n### Backlog\n- Consider adding batch import\n```\n\nExample table-based format:\n```markdown\n| # | Action | Priority | Notes |\n|---|--------|----------|-------|\n| 1 | Fix parser | 1 | Critical |\n| 2 | Update docs | 2 | Nice to have |\n```\n\nAfter testing, clean up any .codeharness/issues.yaml created during verification.\n\n6. Generate proof document at verification/8-2-retro-finding-auto-import-proof.md with evidence from each check.\n7. Run codeharness verify --story 8-2-retro-finding-auto-import to validate the proof format.\n8. Report final result: ALL_PASS (N/N ACs) or PARTIAL (M/N ACs, list failures).\n\nDo NOT use Docker. Do NOT run codeharness stack start. Do NOT start Docker containers.\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commands. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, app startup failures, port conflicts, timeouts)\n- Workarounds applied (alternative run commands, fallback ports, manual process cleanup)\n- Verification gaps (ACs that were hard to verify via runtime interaction, weak evidence)\n- Observations (anything surprising about app behavior, startup time, resource usage)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":149,"cache_read_input_tokens":53485,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":149},"output_tokens":46,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f15b50c-2c9b-40fa-9e63-9fad2199af43","uuid":"15686210-4f8d-4277-a7bc-031ecdd9a515"}
