{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EiUygN4DN1HwPxVMnQyfRX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DQPn5tF7dtw4tv1cYudZQs","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/8-2-retro-finding-auto-import-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: Story 8-2 Retro Finding Auto-Import\n\n**Story:** 8-2-retro-finding-auto-import\n**Verification tier:** runtime-provable\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n\n## Step 1: Build\n\n```\n$ npm run build\nESM ⚡️ Build success in 25ms\nDTS ⚡️ Build success in 889ms\n```\n\n**Result: PASS** — zero errors.\n\n## Step 2: Unit Tests\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run\nTest Files  161 passed (161)\n     Tests  4175 passed (4175)\n```\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run src/commands/__tests__/retro-import.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  36 passed (36)\n```\n\n**Result: PASS** — 4175 tests passed, 36 retro-import tests passed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n### AC1: Fix Now items imported with priority: high\n**PASS** — Ran `codeharness retro-import --epic 99` on section-based retro file with Fix Now items. Output:\n```\n[OK] Imported [issue-001] (high): Fix the broken parser module\n[OK] Imported [issue-002] (high): Update error handling in CLI\n```\nIssues.yaml confirms `priority: high` for both.\n\n### AC2: Fix Soon items imported with priority: medium\n**PASS** — Same run imported Fix Soon item. Output:\n```\n[OK] Imported [issue-003] (medium): Refactor duplicate detection logic\n```\nIssues.yaml confirms `priority: medium`.\n\n### AC3: Backlog items skipped\n**PASS** — Same run logged:\n```\n[INFO] Skipped (backlog — non-actionable): Consider adding batch import\n```\nItem not present in issues.yaml.\n\n### AC4: Duplicate detection on re-run\n**PASS** — Second run of `codeharness retro-import --epic 99` on same file:\n```\n[INFO] Skipped (duplicate of \"Fix the broken parser module\"): Fix the broken parser module\n[INFO] Skipped (duplicate of \"Update error handling in CLI\"): Update error handling in CLI\n[INFO] Skipped (duplicate of \"Refactor duplicate detection logic\"): Refactor duplicate detection logic\n[INFO] Summary: 0 imported, 1 skipped, 3 duplicates\n```\nNo new issues created. Existing issues unmodified.\n\n### AC5: Table-based format fallback\n**PASS** — Ran `codeharness retro-import --epic 98` on table-format retro (`| # | Action | Status | Notes |`). Output:\n```\n[OK] Imported [issue-001] (high): Fix parser regression\n[OK] Imported [issue-002] (medium): Update documentation\n```\n`derivePriority` mapped \"Regressed\" -> high, default -> medium.\n\n### AC6: Source field set correctly\n**PASS** — Issues.yaml shows `source: retro-epic-99` and `source: retro-epic-98` matching the `--epic` flag values.\n\n### AC7: JSON output with counts\n**PASS** — Ran `codeharness retro-import --epic 99 --json`. Output:\n```json\n{\"imported\":3,\"skipped\":1,\"duplicates\":0,\"issues\":[{\"id\":\"issue-001\",\"title\":\"Fix the broken parser module\",\"source\":\"retro-epic-99\",\"priority\":\"high\"},{\"id\":\"issue-002\",\"title\":\"Update error handling in CLI\",\"source\":\"retro-epic-99\",\"priority\":\"high\"},{\"id\":\"issue-003\",\"title\":\"Refactor duplicate detection logic\",\"source\":\"retro-epic-99\",\"priority\":\"medium\"}]}\n```\nContains `imported`, `skipped`, `duplicates` counts and `issues` array with `id`, `title`, `source`, `priority`.\n\n### AC8: Valid YAML file\n**PASS** — `.codeharness/issues.yaml` created with valid YAML structure. Verified readable by `issue list` command:\n```\nissue-001  Fix parser regression  [high]  backlog  (retro-epic-98)\nissue-002  Update documentation  [medium]  backlog  (retro-epic-98)\n```\n\n### AC9: Unit tests exist and pass\n**PASS** — `src/commands/__tests__/retro-import.test.ts` contains 36 tests covering section-based import, table-based fallback, duplicate detection, priority mapping, JSON output, error handling. All pass.\n\n### AC10: Integration with issue-tracker module\n**PASS** — `retro-import.ts` imports `createIssue` and `readIssues` from `../lib/issue-tracker.js`. CLI `issue list` successfully reads issues created by `retro-import`, confirming end-to-end integration.\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Result | Evidence |\n|----|--------|----------|\n| AC1 | PASS | Fix Now -> priority: high in issues.yaml |\n| AC2 | PASS | Fix Soon -> priority: medium in issues.yaml |\n| AC3 | PASS | Backlog items logged as skipped, not in issues.yaml |\n| AC4 | PASS | Re-run detected 3 duplicates, 0 imported |\n| AC5 | PASS | Table format parsed and imported via derivePriority |\n| AC6 | PASS | source: retro-epic-{n} on all imported issues |\n| AC7 | PASS | JSON output has imported/skipped/duplicates/issues |\n| AC8 | PASS | Valid YAML readable by issue list command |\n| AC9 | PASS | 36 unit tests passing |\n| AC10 | PASS | Uses issue-tracker module, issue list reads results |\n\n**Final Result: ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs)**\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2573,"cache_read_input_tokens":33931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2573,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tbq8uvPR9dftszWB5nuigP","session_id":"3f15b50c-2c9b-40fa-9e63-9fad2199af43","uuid":"109fe5c8-a30a-4445-905c-afb1b8ddb65a"}
